<br>
Why they provide such poor service is not necessarily the Guides' fault. May I explain? I will anyway! :p<br>
<br>
When I was a Senior, I was the only Senior on my server for a long time. I did all the Server Management report myself. I logged 30+ hours a week easily, often more. It kept me from leveling my player characters on other servers significantly. I saw would-be gaming partners (and future guild associations) go up in smoke because I couldn't keep pace. BUT, and this is important, I was not resentful of that fact, nor were the Guides who I worked with. Because at that time, Verant was &quot;nice&quot; to us, and we were &quot;nice&quot; to the players. <br>
<br>
Now, that doesn't mean we didn't warn exploiters and actively follow them around so we could warn them enough to get them banned. But it means that players who had corpses in walls, or had them appear under the world, or had them &quot;magically&quot; zone into the lava at known points (yes, the &quot;old time&quot; Guides knew these points), or whatever..... these players got fast and courteous help. Even when we said essentially &quot;no&quot; we tried to be succinct and kind about why.<br>
<br>
But by the time I quit the job (and believe me, it was my second job, next to my paid daytime job) it had gotten to the point that Guides were being handicapped. Let see. We couldn't see the scripts for dynamic quests, not even the Quest Seniors who were tasked with putting them on. So today, how many true dynamic quests (I don't mean stupid &quot;kill all the players&quot; invasions which is all we get anymore) are run? Zero.<br>
What else? The GMs began to be very inconsistant about naming conventions, which is something near and dear to the players. I personally &quot;got&quot; a large number of bad names, but not one of my renames was unwarranted. But the GMs started telling us to leave some bad names alone, but get others. That inconsistancy was daunting to say the least. Then, the written policy to reimburse lost quest items came down, but as we all know, the GMs have inconsistantly followed that policy too. And there is much more dirt which doesn't need to be written down.<br>
<br>
So was the Guide you mention acting properly? Well, certainly a followup reply of &quot;Very sorry we couldn't have gotten to you in time to help :(&quot; would have been called for. But there was indeed nothing at the time the Guide could do. Other than not leave you hanging with no followup reply.<br>
<br>
All the good &quot;old&quot; Guides are gone from CS now. One of the last left after the fiasco at the Faire, which was documented at Lums I think. Are there any good ones today? I'm sure there are. But not enough to provide coverage for a server well enough. As you well know. And the reason is, those who make good Guides have been put off by Scotto and Butler and their minions, to the point that they leave the program in disgust. The ones that are left try, but sometimes its just not enough.<br>
<br>
EQ and Verant CS provide an ample case study of opportunity lost should any future MMOG company want to learn from the past mistakes of the industry.<br>
<br>
And you know, Scotto could have me banned for this, because its more abusive to Verant CS than some things that have gotten players banned. But if he did, it wouldn't change anything I've mentioned. <br>
